paragraphs.name: 187f
paragraphs.text: We left each other on less hostile grounds than you would think. It was as though we had a friendly disagreement. I bought him a Heineken and we joked a little, about our lives and what had just happened.

paragraphs.name: b641
paragraphs.text: He closed his eyes and leaned against the wall, as though my irrationality was so exhausting he needed to take a momentary break from the sense of sight.

paragraphs.name: 173d
paragraphs.text: Like me? I asked.

paragraphs.name: a76d
paragraphs.text: He said: I overreacted, I have “issues,” there is “something wrong with you.” I am ignorant of Dutch culture, weird, too serious, not funny, have no sense of humor. I need help and therapy. I was jealous, and by the way, he didn’t like my ass.
How would you feel if someone grabbed your sister like that? Your mother? I asked.
